text.tspan: Banana Fish by Akimi Yoshida was first published in 1985
and ran through 1994. Fake by Sanami Matoh ran from 1996
to 2000. In the images shown, both manga adhere to the
dark hair/light hair dichotomy, representing a more dominant
and a more submissive character in the relationship. Banana
Fish, which is more romantic rather than sexually explicit,
consists of regular, rectangular panels. Fake, which is con
sidered yaoi and is more sexually explicit, is more visually
dynamic, with irregular shaped panels and bleeds. Compar
ing these two spreads, the panel shapes and plain vs. pat
terned backgrounds lead to a more action packed mood in
Fake compared to Banana Fish. Banana Fish seems more
calm and gentle, which fits in with its more romantic themes.
